// toggle.su — flip a 0/1 GUI state. The 1-s arithmetic IS on the substrate,
// but the state-shuttle is host-resident, not a substrate-state RNN.
//
// flip(s) = 1 - s, computed on the Sutra substrate (make_real lifts the
// result onto the real axis so the host can read it with real()). flip(0)
// returns 1, flip(1) returns 0. The host extracts the scalar via real()
// after each call and passes it to the next click's flip(). So the click
// handler's "state transition" is: host scalar → substrate function call →
// host scalar — stateless function with host carrying state across calls.
//
// This is the same host-state-shuttle pattern font.su's cycle_step and
// count.su's step use; the 2026-05-27 audit (planning/27-substrate-honesty-
// audit-2026-05-27.md) flagged all three. A real substrate-state version
// would keep the toggle state as a vector across clicks. Queued.
function vector flip(scalar s) { return make_real(1.0 - s); }

function vector main() { return flip(0.0); }
